Definition R_universe_instance R :=
  fun u u' => Forall2 R (List.map Universe.make u) (List.map Universe.make u').
Cumulative inductive types:
To simplify the development, we allow the variance list to not exactly match the instances, so as to keep syntactic equality an equivalence relation even on ill-formed terms. It corresponds to the right notion on well-formed terms. 
Definition R_universe_variance (Re Rle : Universe.t -> Universe.t -> Prop) v u u' :=
  match v with
  | Variance.Irrelevant => True
  | Variance.Covariant => Rle (Universe.make u) (Universe.make u')
  | Variance.Invariant => Re (Universe.make u) (Universe.make u')
  end.

Fixpoint R_universe_instance_variance Re Rle v u u' :=
  match u, u' return Prop with
  | u :: us, u' :: us' =>
    match v with
    | [] => R_universe_instance_variance Re Rle v us us' 
      (* Missing variance stands for irrelevance, we still check that the instances have
        the same length. *)
    | v :: vs => R_universe_variance Re Rle v u u' /\
        R_universe_instance_variance Re Rle vs us us'
    end
  | [], [] => True
  | _, _ => False
  end.

Definition lookup_minductive Œ£ mind :=
  match lookup_env Œ£ mind with
  | Some (InductiveDecl decl) => Some decl
  | _ => None
  end.

Definition lookup_inductive Œ£ ind :=
  match lookup_minductive Œ£ (inductive_mind ind) with
  | Some mdecl => 
    match nth_error mdecl.(ind_bodies) (inductive_ind ind) with
    | Some idecl => Some (mdecl, idecl)
    | None => None
    end
  | None => None
  end.

Definition lookup_constructor Œ£ ind k :=
  match lookup_inductive Œ£ ind with
  | Some (mdecl, idecl) => 
    match nth_error idecl.(ind_ctors) k with
    | Some cdecl => Some (mdecl, idecl, cdecl)
    | None => None
    end
  | _ => None
  end.

Definition global_variance Œ£ gr napp :=
  match gr with
  | IndRef ind =>
    match lookup_inductive Œ£ ind with
    | Some (mdecl, idecl) => 
      match destArity [] idecl.(ind_type) with
      | Some (ctx, _) => if (context_assumptions ctx) <=? napp then mdecl.(ind_variance)
        else None
      | None => None
      end
    | None => None
    end
  | ConstructRef ind k =>
    match lookup_constructor Œ£ ind k with
    | Some (mdecl, idecl, cdecl) =>
      if (cdecl.(cstr_arity) + mdecl.(ind_npars))%nat <=? napp then
        (** Fully applied constructors are always compared at the same supertype, 
          which implies that no universe equality needs to be checked here. *)
        Some []
      else None
    | _ => None
    end
  | _ => None
  end.

Definition R_opt_variance Re Rle v :=
  match v with 
  | Some v => R_universe_instance_variance Re Rle v
  | None => R_universe_instance Re
  end.

Definition R_global_instance Œ£ Re Rle gr napp :=
  R_opt_variance Re Rle (global_variance Œ£ gr napp).

Syntactic equality up-to universes

We don't look at printing annotations
Equality is indexed by a natural number that counts the number of applications that surround the current term, used to implement cumulativity of inductive types correctly (only fully applied constructors and inductives benefit from it). 
Inductive eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ (Re Rle : Universe.t -> Universe.t -> Prop) (napp : nat) : term -> term -> Type :=
| eq_Rel n  :
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tRel n) (tRel n)

| eq_Evar e args args' :
    All2 (eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0) args args' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tEvar e args) (tEvar e args')

| eq_Var id :
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tVar id) (tVar id)

| eq_Sort s s' :
    Rle s s' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tSort s) (tSort s')

| eq_App t t' u u' :
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle (#|u| + napp) t t' ->
    All2 (eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0) u u' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tApp t u) (tApp t' u')

| eq_Const c u u' :
    R_universe_instance Re u u' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tConst c u) (tConst c u')

| eq_Ind i u u' :
    R_global_instance Œ£ Re Rle (IndRef i) napp u u' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tInd i u) (tInd i u')

| eq_Construct i k u u' :
    R_global_instance Œ£ Re Rle (ConstructRef i k) napp u u' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tConstruct i k u) (tConstruct i k u')

| eq_Lambda na na' ty ty' t t' :
    eq_binder_annot na na' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 ty ty' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle 0 t t' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tLambda na ty t) (tLambda na' ty' t')

| eq_Prod na na' a a' b b' :
    eq_binder_annot na na' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 a a' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle 0 b b' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tProd na a b) (tProd na' a' b')

| eq_LetIn na na' t t' ty ty' u u' :
    eq_binder_annot na na' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 t t' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 ty ty' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle 0 u u' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tLetIn na t ty u) (tLetIn na' t' ty' u')

| eq_Case ind p p' c c' brs brs' :
    All2 (eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0) p.(pparams) p'.(pparams) ->
    R_universe_instance Re p.(puinst) p'.(puinst) ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 p.(preturn) p'.(preturn) ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 c c' ->
    All2 (fun x y =>
      bcontext x = bcontext y √ó
      eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 (bbody x) (bbody y)
    ) brs brs' ->
  eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tCase ind p c brs) (tCase ind p' c' brs')

| eq_Proj p c c' :
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 c c' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tProj p c) (tProj p c')

| eq_Fix mfix mfix' idx :
    All2 (fun x y =>
      eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 x.(dtype) y.(dtype) *
      eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 x.(dbody) y.(dbody) *
      (x.(rarg) = y.(rarg)) *
      eq_binder_annot x.(dname) y.(dname)
    )%type mfix mfix' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tFix mfix idx) (tFix mfix' idx)

| eq_CoFix mfix mfix' idx :
    All2 (fun x y =>
      eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 x.(dtype) y.(dtype) *
      eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 x.(dbody) y.(dbody) *
      (x.(rarg) = y.(rarg)) *
      eq_binder_annot x.(dname) y.(dname)
    ) mfix mfix' ->
    eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tCoFix mfix idx) (tCoFix mfix' idx)
    
| eq_Cast t1 c t2 t1' c' t2' :
  eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 t1 t1' ->
  eq_cast_kind c c' ->
  eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Re 0 t2 t2' ->
  eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tCast t1 c t2) (tCast t1' c' t2')

| eq_Int i : eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tInt i) (tInt i)
| eq_Float f : eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle napp (tFloat f) (tFloat f).

Notation eq_term_upto_univ Œ£ Re Rle := (eq_term_upto_univ_napp Œ£ Re Rle 0).

(* ** Syntactic conversion up-to universes *)

Definition eq_term `{checker_flags} Œ£ œÜ :=
  eq_term_upto_univ Œ£ (eq_universe œÜ) (eq_universe œÜ).

(* ** Syntactic cumulativity up-to universes *)

Definition leq_term `{checker_flags} Œ£ œÜ :=
  eq_term_upto_univ Œ£ (eq_universe œÜ) (leq_universe œÜ).

    congruence.
Qed.

Lemma eq_term_leq_term `{checker_flags} Œ£ œÜ napp t u :

hle:RelationClasses.subrelation Rle Rle'

| Some v => R_universe_instance_variance Re Rle v
| None => R_universe_instance Re
end t t' ->

| Some v => R_universe_instance_variance Re' Rle' v
| None => R_universe_instance Re'
end t t'
